sequenceDiagram
    actor User
    participant Frontend as Frontend (React)
    participant API as Backend API
    participant Controller as productController
    participant DB as MongoDB

    User->>Frontend: Enter keyword (e.g., "rice")
    User->>Frontend: Optionally set filters (category, price range)
    Frontend->>API: GET /api/products?keyword=rice&pageNumber=1
    activate API
    API->>Controller: getProducts(req.query)
    activate Controller
    Note over Controller: Current backend applies regex on name and pagination
    Controller->>DB: Product.countDocuments({ name: { $regex, $options: 'i' } })
    Controller->>DB: Product.find({ name: { $regex, $options: 'i' } }).limit(pageSize).skip(offset)
    DB-->>Controller: Matching products, count
    Controller-->>API: { products, page, pages }
    deactivate Controller
    API-->>Frontend: JSON response with paginated products
    deactivate API
    Frontend-->>User: Display results and pagination controls

